Hey Raptor05121, yes the exe. file upload would be great to upload. In my past experience, the only way the new carenado planes would work, is if you upload and install it through the exe. file. That'll be much appreciated.

The best way to capture a rip is to make a fake FSX folder, copy the FSX app into the folder, then point the installer at that folder. That will capture SimObjects (planes) gauges, modules, proprietary .dll's in the publishers folder (C:Program Files (x86)Microsoft GamesMicrosoft Flight Simulator XCarenado, for example) and anything that is installed within the FSX folder. It will not capture .dll's or .lic files hidden within the Windows, ProgramData or Appdata folders; these are some of the places publishers like Flight1 place their security files.

Some parts of the aircraft are invisible. It's because some dlls are missing, in places like app data, and system folders... You just can fix it if you send us the installer of the aircraft, not just the folders! Thanks a lot!
